This guide explains how to integrate and use the .clouds CSS class in Elementor Pro to create an animated cloud effect across the width of your website.

Class: .clouds
This CSS class animates an element (clouds) across the screen, from left to right. The clouds will have a slight opacity and will continuously animate, creating a smooth visual effect

How to Implement:
Add the .clouds CSS Class:

Simply assign the .clouds class to any Elementor element where you want the animated clouds.
Custom CSS:

Paste the CSS code into Custom CSS in Elementor Pro.
Notes:
Speed: Adjust using --i in the elementâ€™s style attribute.
Positioning: Ensure the element has position: relative; if needed.
Opacity: Change in the .clouds class for visibility adjustments.